    • Method Detail

      • build_Command_From_Selection

        public static void build_Command_From_Selection(String filetype,
                                                String organ)
        This static method takes the user input - file selected for processing and the organ type and file type - it builds the shell command that will be called to execute the processing script in Blender using this information and creates a new file name for the processing mesh.
        Parameters:
        filetype - String that specifies file format to convert .stl. This is either 'fbx' or 'glb' and is set via combobox in GUI. Default is 'glb'
        organ - String that specifies type of organ the mesh is. This controls the material that is applied.

      • process_Command

        public static String process_Command(String command2)
                              throws InterruptedException,
                                     IOException
        This static method takes the String command passed to it and executes this in shell by calling Runtime.getRuntime().exec(command). It checks for output from the shell and if not as expected - alerts user about file problem. It also catches IOException (If Blender or the processing script cannot be found) and InteruptedException.
        Parameters:
        command2 - The String shell command that will be executed.
        Returns:
        The String output from shell.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException
        IOException
